The therapeutic benefits of cannabis are more and more recognized at the scientific level (
 Bar-Lev Schleider et al., 2018; 
 Freeman et al., 2019; 
 Levinsohn and Hill, 2020), and regulation have to consider the evolution of its use (
 Zaami et al., 2018; 
 Corli et al., 2019; 
 Brunetti et al., 2020). There are several listed medical indications in Italy, which should be treated accordingly with different cannabis varieties containing tetrahydrocannabinol (THC), cannabidiol (CBD), or both of them (
 Law 9/11/2015, 279 Official Gazette; 
 Ministero della Salute, 2017; 
 EMCDA, 2018).
